Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}(halved and peeled), then chop each half into quarters. Halve the @apple{1}(halved and cored), remove the core and chop each half into three wedges (no need to peel).

Trim the @carrot{3}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pick the @sage{1/2%bunch}(leaves picked and roughly chopped) from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the onion, apple, carrot and sage onto another large baking tray and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

Wrap one rasher of @British streaky bacon{4%rasher(s)} around each @British honey mustard sausages{4}.

Starting at the top, spiral the bacon down the sausage so that it covers the whole thing. Place the sausages on top of the veg, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the veg is tender and the sausages are cooked through, ~{30-35%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

About ~{5%minutes} before the sausages and veg are cooked, pop a small #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Add the @onion marmalade{40%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml} to the pan. Stir together and bring to the boil, then remove from the heat and stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then set aside.

When everything's cooked, add the roast potatoes to the sausage and veg tray. Mix everything together.

Reheat the buttery sauce if necessary.

Share the roasted veg and pigs in blankets between your plates. Spoon over the buttery sauce to finish.

Enjoy!